(41, 6, 41, 41, 14, 22, 22, 'blessed, and brake the loaves', 'Connection of Blessing and Breaking Bread', 'Both passages emphasize the act of taking bread, blessing it, and breaking it. This connection highlights the significance of Jesus'' actions in providing sustenance and establishing a new meaning for bread.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 41, 43, 11, 41, 41, 'looked up to heaven', 'Connection of Gratitude and Blessing', 'Both passages emphasize the act of looking up and expressing gratitude. In Mark, Jesus looks up to heaven before blessing the loaves, while in John, He lifts His eyes to thank the Father.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 41, 46, 10, 31, 31, 'blessed', 'Glorifying God in Actions', 'This connection highlights the act of giving thanks and blessing food in Mark 6:41, which aligns with the call in 1 Corinthians 10:31 to do all things for the glory of God. Both passages emphasize the importance of recognizing God''s provision and dedicating our actions to Him.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 42, 41, 8, 8, 9, 'and were filled', 'Feeding of the Multitudes', 'Both passages emphasize the act of eating and being filled, showcasing Jesus'' miraculous provision for large crowds. The repetition of being ''filled'' connects the two events of feeding the multitudes.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 42, 42, 9, 17, 17, 'and were filled', 'Feeding of the Multitude', 'Both passages emphasize the act of eating and being filled, highlighting the miraculous provision of food. Additionally, the mention of fragments in Luke connects to the completeness of the meal in Mark.', 'parallel', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 42, 40, 14, 20, 21, 'they did all eat, and were filled', 'Feeding of the Five Thousand', 'Both passages emphasize the act of eating and being filled, highlighting the miraculous provision of food. The mention of the number of people fed in Matthew further underscores the significance of this event.', 'parallel', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 42, 40, 15, 37, 38, 'they did all eat, and were filled', 'Feeding of the Multitude', 'Both passages emphasize the act of feeding a large crowd, highlighting that all present were satisfied. The phrase ''they did all eat, and were filled'' appears in both accounts, reinforcing the miraculous provision of food.', 'parallel', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 42, 43, 6, 12, 12, 'were filled', 'Connection of Fulfillment and Gathering', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of being filled after a meal. The act of gathering fragments in John 6:12 follows the fulfillment described in Mark 6:42, highlighting the importance of not wasting what has been provided.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 42, 12, 4, 42, 44, NULL, 'Feeding Miracles Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the miraculous provision of food, where a small amount satisfies a large group. The phrase ''they did eat, and were filled'' in Mark echoes the outcome of the feeding in 2 Kings, highlighting God''s ability to provide abundantly.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 42, 5, 8, 3, 3, 'and were filled', 'Connection of Divine Provision', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of divine provision for physical needs. Mark 6:42 describes the fulfillment of hunger through Jesus, while Deuteronomy 8:3 highlights God''s provision of manna to teach reliance on His word.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 43, 41, 8, 19, 20, NULL, 'Connection of Basket Fragments', 'Both passages emphasize the collection of fragments after feeding the multitudes, highlighting the miraculous provision. The specific mention of ''baskets full of fragments'' in both instances connects the two events.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 45, 40, 14, 22, 33, 'he constrained his disciples to get into the ship', 'Disciples in the Ship', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus constraining his disciples to get into a ship and go to the other side. This shared action sets the stage for the miraculous events that follow in both accounts.', 'parallel', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 45, 43, 6, 15, 21, 'get into the ship', 'Disciples in a Ship', 'Both passages emphasize the disciples entering a ship to cross the sea. In Mark, they are sent away by Jesus, while in John, they go down to the sea after Jesus departs. This connection highlights the shared experience of the disciples in navigating the sea.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 45, 41, 6, 32, 32, NULL, 'Departure by Ship', 'Both passages emphasize the act of departing by ship. In Mark 6:32, the disciples leave for a desert place, while in Mark 6:45, they are constrained to get into the ship to go to the other side.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 45, 41, 8, 22, 22, 'unto Bethsaida', 'Journey to Bethsaida', 'Both passages emphasize the location of Bethsaida, where Jesus sends his disciples and later arrives to heal a blind man. This connection highlights the significance of Bethsaida as a setting for Jesus'' ministry and miracles.', 'theme', 0.3, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 45, 40, 11, 21, 21, 'Bethsaida', 'Connection Between Bethsaida References', 'Both passages emphasize Bethsaida, highlighting its significance in Jesus'' ministry. Mark mentions the disciples going to Bethsaida, while Matthew pronounces woe upon it for its lack of repentance despite witnessing mighty works.', 'theme', 0.293, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 45, 42, 10, 13, 13, 'Bethsaida', 'Connection Between Bethsaida References', 'Both passages emphasize Bethsaida, highlighting its significance in Jesus'' ministry. Mark mentions the disciples going to the other side before unto Bethsaida, while Luke pronounces woe upon the city for its unrepentance despite witnessing mighty works.', 'theme', 0.293, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 46, 41, 1, 35, 35, NULL, 'Jesus'' Solitary Prayer Practices', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' practice of seeking solitude for prayer. In each instance, he departs to a solitary place to engage in prayer, highlighting the importance of personal communion with God.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 46, 40, 6, 6, 6, 'departed into a mountain to pray', 'Connection of Prayer Practices', 'This connection highlights the importance of private prayer. Both passages emphasize the act of seeking solitude for communication with God.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 46, 42, 6, 12, 12, 'into a mountain to pray', 'Connection of Prayer in Mountains', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus going into a mountain to pray, highlighting the significance of solitude and prayer in His ministry. The act of praying in a mountainous setting is a shared theme that underscores His reliance on communication with God.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 46, 40, 14, 23, 23, NULL, 'Connection of Prayer in Solitude', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' action of going up into a mountain to pray after sending people away. This highlights a shared theme of seeking solitude for prayer.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 46, 60, 2, 21, 21, NULL, 'Example of Christ''s Prayer Life', 'This connection highlights the importance of Christ''s example in prayer and suffering. Both passages emphasize the call to follow Christ''s steps, which includes seeking solitude for prayer as seen in Mark 6:46.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 6, 47, 40, 14, 23, 23, NULL, 'Evening Solitude of Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of Jesus being alone in the evening. In Mark, he is ''alone on the land,'' while in Matthew, he is ''there alone'' after sending the multitudes away.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
